                            <comment id="13797229" author="myrna" created="Wed, 16 Oct 2013 21:40:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Glenn, is it possible for you to attach a reproducible test case or at least a derby stack trace?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13797265" author="glennmcg" created="Wed, 16 Oct 2013 22:18:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;All of the stack trace that&apos;s in derby code is present in the issue. The next frame points at the spot in my code that invokes getWarnings on a PreparedStatement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A runnable unit test would take a fair bit of work to generate, as the actual code would be hard to extract.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, here&apos;s some pseudo-code&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;open connection&lt;br/&gt;
create preparedStatement  &amp;#8212; DELETE FROM testJdbcAcct WHERE NAS_IP_Address = ? AND NAS_Port = ? AND Acct_Session_Id = ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;loop&lt;br/&gt;
   invoke ps.set on args&lt;br/&gt;
   ps.addBatch&lt;br/&gt;
endloop&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ps.executeBatch()&lt;br/&gt;
ps.getWarnings();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All of the deletes were intended to fail for this test.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13797814" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 17 Oct 2013 12:52:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a repro. Full stack trace on trunk:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.NullPointerException
	at org.apache.derby.client.am.SqlWarning.getSQLWarning(SqlWarning.java:84)
	at org.apache.derby.client.am.ClientStatement.getWarnings(ClientStatement.java:916)
	at D6373.main(D6373.java:15)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13797823" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 17 Oct 2013 13:09:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it is more reasonable that client.am.SqlWarning.getSQLWarning() builds the SQLWarning based on the warning chain and not on the exception chain it inherits from its base class client.am.SqlException. I&apos;ll try to come up with a patch for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also note that the current regression tests don&apos;t seem to exercise the code that constructs chained warnings: &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Derby-JaCoCo/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/coverage-report/org.apache.derby.client.am/SqlWarning.java.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Derby-JaCoCo/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/coverage-report/org.apache.derby.client.am/SqlWarning.java.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13797927" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 17 Oct 2013 15:10:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch makes SqlWarning.getSQLWarning() follow the warning chain instead of the exception chain. Since it has already checked that the warning chain is not null, the NPE is avoided.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch also adds a test case which verifies that the NPE is no longer thrown, and that all the warnings from the batch are received on the client. (The behaviour seems to be slightly different on embedded. It has only a single warning on the statement after executing the batch. The client has one warning for each of the statements in the batch that got a warning.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All regression tests ran cleanly with the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13798211" author="kmarsden" created="Thu, 17 Oct 2013 19:12:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is marked as a regression and the user indicated the problem case worked with 10.8.2.2, but the repro program throws an NPE all the way  back to 10.1.1.1 so doesn&apos;t look like a regression at least with regard to the reproduction attached. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13798967" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2013 10:56:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;In my environment, the repro fails with client versions down to 10.2.1.6, and passes if the client version is 10.1.x.y. The method in which the NPE is thrown was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-840&quot; title=&quot;International messages DatabaseMetaData to GetFileInputStreamAction in org.apache.derby.client.am&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-840&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-840&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in Derby 10.2.1.6.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13799116" author="kmarsden" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2013 15:05:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I see that now. I must have made an error in my testing, but it is curious Glenn seemed to indicate some change since 10.8.2.2.   Regardless, your fix looks good. Hopefully, it  will fix Glenn&apos;s scenario.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13801555" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 22 Oct 2013 08:14:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1534523 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=knutanders&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;knutanders&quot;&gt;Knut Anders Hatlen&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;code/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1534523&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1534523&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6373&quot; title=&quot;NPE in Statement.getWarnings()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-6373&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-6373&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: NPE in Statement.getWarnings()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13801577" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 22 Oct 2013 08:37:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Kathey. I&apos;ve checked in the fix. java.sql.SQLWarning and java.sql.SQLException actually have one shared chain, so one possible improvement might be to make client.am.SqlWarning and client.am.SqlException have a single, shared one too. But I think this minimal fix is OK for now, and sufficient for back-porting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13801591" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 22 Oct 2013 09:01:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;If I change the repro to use a PreparedStatement instead of a Statement, I don&apos;t see the NPE if the server version is 10.8.2.2, but I do see it if the server version is 10.9.1.0 or 10.10.1.1. The patch fixes the NPE for the PreparedStatement case too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this means something was fixed in the server code in 10.9 that made the warnings propagate to the client, and that it worked on 10.8.2.2 simply because the client didn&apos;t get the warnings and didn&apos;t exercise the buggy code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13801675" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 22 Oct 2013 11:13:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like it changed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-129&quot; title=&quot;Derby should throw a truncation error or warning when CASTing a parameter/constant to char or char for bit datatypes and the data is too large for the datatype.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-129&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-129&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The server sent the warnings to the client even before that fix, but it gave them sqlcode 100, which the client sometimes ignores (sqlcode 100 is used by the network protocol to mark end of data). After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-129&quot; title=&quot;Derby should throw a truncation error or warning when CASTing a parameter/constant to char or char for bit datatypes and the data is too large for the datatype.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-129&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-129&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; a different sqlcode is used for warnings that should not be ignored by the client, and the client will always see them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13804044" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 24 Oct 2013 11:39:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1535335 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=knutanders&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;knutanders&quot;&gt;Knut Anders Hatlen&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;code/branches/10.10&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1535335&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1535335&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6373&quot; title=&quot;NPE in Statement.getWarnings()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-6373&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-6373&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: NPE in Statement.getWarnings()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Merged revision 1534523 from trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
